    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-06-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-06-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="323"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d323">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Swenson</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-06-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 6, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 261.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                        cablegram<note n="a" xml:id="d323fna">Printed, <ref target="#pg_6">page
                            6</ref>.</note> of the 21th ultimo.</p>
                <p>In reply to a request which I addressed to the foreign office, under date of the
                    26th ultimo, the minister of foreign affairs informs me, in a note of the 3d
                    instant, that the Danish Government grants the desired permission.</p>
                <p>I have so notified our consular officers in Denmark proper and in the Danish West
                    Indies.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Laurits S. Swenson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
